results.wikipedia_summary: The magpie-robins or shamas (from shama, Hindi for C. malabaricus) are medium-sized insectivorous birds (some also eat berries and other fruit) in the genera Copsychus and Trichixos. They were formerly in the thrush family Turdidae, but are more often now treated as part of the Old World flycatcher Muscicapidae. The Seychelles Magpie-Robin is one of the most endangered birds in the world, with a population of less than 250, although this is a notable increase from...
